  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [x] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (5385486 2022-06-27T00:03:53.397337486Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n`forge coverage`\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThere is a difference in output when running a `forge coverage` on Windows vs on Linux. I believe this is due to the difference in directory separators on win/unix systems.\r\n\r\nWindows:\r\n\r\n- quasi-alternating `/` and `\\`:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/175921350-2f525f4f-766e-4532-be36-073ca18e1ea2.png)\r\n\r\n- coverage reports wrongfully at 0%:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/175921555-f76b5f13-f097-4d5a-8c15-bd370caf85e1.png)\r\n\r\n- it doesn't appear to be the case that a directory with '/' has (no) coverage and vice-versa:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/175921965-9296ea0a-d5e2-4057-a520-2074f5dcf714.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLinux:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/175921430-ddd1409c-8858-4ea2-b962-62104973f6d0.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/175921574-bf97b7d5-6b4b-4615-8f41-c211bc41322b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nBoth screenshots come from the same machine, same files, ... The tests are not in the same order upon runs on the different machines, this might be another small tweak.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
